text: I graduated with an honors diploma from KMHS as part of the class of 2022. During my time at KM I made the honers role every year and was a Dick Ohm recipient all 4 years at the High School. Over my time at KMHS I was on the Robotics Team, the Boys Cross Country team, the Chess club, the ECO club, and the Honors Society. I graduated with a weighted GPA of 4.117 (w/bonus points 4.542).

The Kettle Moraine IT internship program is an opportunity to work the technology help desk at Kettle Moraine High and be deployed to classrooms if necessary. You can work on making guides for equipment and computers in the need of software or hardware repair are shipped in from the districts elementary and middle schools. It is a great way to get experience troubleshooting computer problems, filling out support tickets, replacing parts, and working with clients. I was in the program for four terms, one freshman, one junior, and two for my senior year.
